NK spy indicted after coming to South in disguise as defector
SEOUL, Jan. 5 (Yonhap) -- Prosecutors on Thursday indicted an alleged North Korean spy suspected of impersonating a defector seeking to settle in South Korea. The 47-year-old man surnamed Kim, believed to be a former agent of the North's military intelligence unit, was charged with entering South Korea in June last year on a mission of pro-North espionage, according to the prosecutors.